'''Deroy d'Encarnação Duarte''' ({{IPA|nl|də.ˈɾɔj|lang}} {{IPA|pt|dẽ.kɐɾ.nɐ.ˈsɐ̃w du.ˈaɾ.tɨ|lang}}; born 4 July 1999) is a professional [[association football|football]] player who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[First Professional Football League (Bulgaria)|Bulgarian First League]] club [[PFC Ludogorets Razgrad|Ludogorets Razgrad]].<ref name="WF">{{WorldFootball.net|deroy-duarte}}</ref> Born in the Netherlands, he represents the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]].

==Club career==
===Sparta Rotterdam===
Duarte played youth football for [[Sparta Rotterdam]]. As the [[Tweede Divisie]] was reintroduced, he began playing regularly for [[Sparta Rotterdam|Jong Sparta Rotterdam]] who had joined the [[Dutch football league system]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Plannen tweede divisie gaan door |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2006876-plannen-tweede-divisie-gaan-door |access-date=20 April 2023 |work=NOS |date=2 December 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221210145319/https://nos.nl/artikel/2006876-plannen-tweede-divisie-gaan-door |archive-date=10 December 2022 |language=nl}}</ref><ref name="WF" /> In the [[2016–17 Eredivisie|2016–17 season]], he was on Sparta's first-team bench for a few games without making an appearance.<ref name="WF" />

He made his professional debut for Sparta in the [[2017–18 Eredivisie|2017–18 season]], replacing [[Stijn Spierings]] in the 81st minute of a 3–0 away loss to [[VVV-Venlo]].<ref>{{cite web |title=VVV vs. Sparta Rotterdam – 12 August 2017 |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2017/08/12/netherlands/eredivisie/vvv-venlo/sparta-rotterdam-bv/2462339/ |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=20 April 2023}}</ref> Sparta was relegated to the [[Eerste Divisie]] that season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Advocaat en Sparta ontgoocheld: 'We zijn het niet waard' |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2232777-advocaat-en-sparta-ontgoocheld-we-zijn-het-niet-waard |access-date=20 April 2023 |work=NOS |date=20 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230408220911/https://nos.nl/artikel/2232777-advocaat-en-sparta-ontgoocheld-we-zijn-het-niet-waard |archive-date=8 April 2023 |language=nl}}</ref> However, he was part of the team that finished second and returned to the Eredivisie after winning the promotion play-off against [[TOP Oss]] and [[De Graafschap]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Sparta en RKC promoveren dankzij bizarre comebacks naar Eredivisie |url=https://www.nu.nl/voetbal/5913312/sparta-en-rkc-promoveren-dankzij-bizarre-comebacks-naar-eredivisie.html |access-date=20 April 2023 |work=NU |date=28 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200927162539/https://www.nu.nl/voetbal/5913312/sparta-en-rkc-promoveren-dankzij-bizarre-comebacks-naar-eredivisie.html |archive-date=27 September 2020 |language=nl}}</ref>

In the following [[2019–20 Eredivisie|2019–20 season]], he was mainly a substitute, with his brother [[Laros Duarte]] among the players ahead of him in the pecking order.<ref name="WF" /><ref name="ELF">{{cite news |last1=Beck |first1=Tim |title=De Duarte-broers: een ander pad, hetzelfde reisdoel |url=https://www.elfvoetbal.nl/binnenland/280139/de-duarte-broers-een-ander-pad-hetzelfde-reisdoel |access-date=20 April 2023 |work=ELF Voetbal |date=25 January 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210125193154/https://www.elfvoetbal.nl/binnenland/280139/de-duarte-broers-een-ander-pad-hetzelfde-reisdoel |archive-date=25 January 2021 |language=nl}}</ref> However, he established himself as a regular starter in his fifth and final season at Sparta, during the [[2020–21 Eredivisie|2020–21 season]].<ref name="WF" /> His contract with Sparta expired in June 2021, with Duarte having scored a total of 13 goals in 115 appearances for the club.<ref name="WF" />

===Fortuna Sittard===
On 12 August 2021, Duarte signed a three-year contract with [[Fortuna Sittard]], who acquired him on a free transfer from Sparta.<ref>{{cite web |title=Fortuna versterkt middenveld met Deroy Duarte |url=https://fortunasittard.nl/fortuna-sittard-versterkt-middenveld-met-deroy-duarte/ |website=Fortuna Sittard |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210812172656/https://fortunasittard.nl/fortuna-sittard-versterkt-middenveld-met-deroy-duarte/ |archive-date=12 August 2021 |language=nl |date=12 August 2021 |url-status=dead}}</ref> Two days later, he made his debut in the season opener against [[FC Twente|Twente]], which was won 2–1.<ref>{{cite web |title=Fortuna Sittard – FC Twente 2:1 (Eredivisie 2021/2022, 1. Round) |url=https://www.worldfootball.net/match-report/ma9232693/lineup/ |website=WorldFootball.net |publisher=HEIM:SPIEL |access-date=20 April 2023}}</ref> On 26 February 2022, he scored his first goal for the club against [[SC Cambuur|Cambuur]].<ref>{{cite news |title=VAR frustreert Fortuna, waarna duel kantelt en Cambuur dankzij Boere nog wint |url=https://nos.nl/artikel/2419032-var-frustreert-fortuna-waarna-duel-kantelt-en-cambuur-dankzij-boere-nog-wint |access-date=20 April 2023 |work=NOS |date=26 February 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230330102131/https://nos.nl/artikel/2419032-var-frustreert-fortuna-waarna-duel-kantelt-en-cambuur-dankzij-boere-nog-wint |archive-date=30 March 2023 |language=nl}}</ref>

===Ludogorets Razgrad===
In June 2024, he moved to Bulgaria, joining [[PFC Ludogorets Razgrad|Ludogorets Razgrad]].<ref name="DeroyDuarteLudogoretsRazgrad2024">{{cite web|author=Mladenova, Kremena|publisher=bta.bg|language=Bulgarian| title=Лудогорец представи официално новите си попълнения Дуарте и Куртулуш|url=https://www.bta.bg/bg/news/sport/696174-ludogorets-predstavi-ofitsialno-novite-si-popalneniya-duarte-i-kurtulush|date=24 June 2024|access-date=20 August 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in the Netherlands, Duarte is of Cape Verdean descent. He was called up to represent the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]] for a set of friendlies in March 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abola.pt/Africa/2022-03-17/cabo-verde-bebe-estreia-se-em-convocatorias-dos-tubaroes-azuis/https%3a%2f%2fwww.abola.pt%2fAfrica%2f2022-03-17%2fcabo-verde-bebe-estreia-se-em-convocatorias-dos-tubaroes-azuis%2f932347|title=Bebé estreia-se em convocatórias dos Tubarões Azuis (Cabo Verde)|website=A Bola|access-date=2022-03-24|archive-date=2023-07-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230726125023/https://www.abola.pt/Africa/2022-03-17/cabo-verde-bebe-estreia-se-em-convocatorias-dos-tubaroes-azuis/https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abola.pt%2FAfrica%2F2022-03-17%2Fcabo-verde-bebe-estreia-se-em-convocatorias-dos-tubaroes-azuis%2F932347|url-status=dead}}</ref> He debuted with Cape Verde in a 2–0 friendly win over [[Guadeloupe national football team|Guadeloupe]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.besoccer.com/match/seleccion-guadalupe/cabo-verde/2022433474/events|title=Live events Guadalupe vs Cape Verde – International Friendly 2022|website=besoccer.com}}</ref>

==Personal life==
He is the younger brother of the footballer [[Laros Duarte]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=CrioloSports|url=http://criolosports.com/index.php/criolos-no-estrangeiro/2878-criolos-no-estrangeiro-deroy-duarte-renova-com-sparta-rotterdam|title=Creoles Abroad: Deroy Duarte renews with Sparta Rotterdam|language=Portuguese|date=8 August 2017|access-date=20 September 2017|archive-date=13 December 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191213222110/http://criolosports.com/index.php/criolos-no-estrangeiro/2878-criolos-no-estrangeiro-deroy-duarte-renova-com-sparta-rotterdam|url-status=dead}}</ref>

